253
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,360
Tell her I'm back in Shenzhen.

254
00:14:59,039 --> 00:15:00,360
I went to Shenzhen. Can you remember that?

255
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:01,519
Sure.

256
00:15:06,559 --> 00:15:08,159
- Did you disable the CCTV? - A long time ago.

257
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:09,919
Hide it. Stop drinking.

258
00:15:10,279 --> 00:15:11,600
- Don't open the door. - Stop drinking.

259
00:15:21,559 --> 00:15:22,559
Shi Yi.

260
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:24,080
I'm here to pack up.

261
00:15:28,039 --> 00:15:29,519
I didn't see that coming.

262
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:32,080
It's all for the best.

263
00:15:32,679 --> 00:15:33,919
Where's Hou Jue?

264
00:15:33,919 --> 00:15:35,000
Did he leave?

265
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:36,480
He has left.

266
00:15:38,039 --> 00:15:39,039
Let's go.

267
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,480
Do you need my help?

268
00:16:00,679 --> 00:16:02,240
No, I can do it myself.

269
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:09,200
I'm leaving.

270
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,480
I feel a little reluctant to leave.

271
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,840
Why do you feel reluctant?

272
00:16:15,759 --> 00:16:17,519
He didn't feel bad leaving you behind.

273
00:16:20,559 --> 00:16:21,799
I didn't say that I'm reluctant to leave him.

274
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,320
I mean...

275
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:24,440
That's enough.

276
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,320
You're not a bodyguard here.

277
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:28,320
I'm not Ms. Qian either. You can tell the truth now.

278
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:35,240
All right.

279
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,200
That's true.

280
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,120
I'm worried about him.

281
00:16:41,679 --> 00:16:43,440
You are worried about him,

282
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,679
but he is not worried about you.

283
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:50,000
He ran away for the greater good.

284
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,480
He doesn't care about you.

285
00:16:51,879 --> 00:16:54,159
I told you on your first day as a bodyguard.

286
00:16:54,159 --> 00:16:56,919
Don't get personal at work.

287
00:16:57,039 --> 00:16:58,080
I know.

288
00:16:58,759 --> 00:17:00,120
But how can living humans...

289
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:02,480
not have any feelings for each other?

290
00:17:03,279 --> 00:17:04,839
In the beginning, I was annoyed by him too.

291
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:06,410
He behaved...

292
00:17:07,039 --> 00:17:08,359
like a spoiled brat.

293
00:17:08,599 --> 00:17:09,839
He's really self-centered.

294
00:17:10,890 --> 00:17:12,039
Then I found out...

295
00:17:12,359 --> 00:17:13,440
I misunderstood him.

296
00:17:15,039 --> 00:17:16,170
How is that so?

297
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:20,720
He looks playful on the outside...

298
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,200
but actually is very kind on the inside.

299
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,720
Have you seen any rich guys...

300
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,440
volunteering in rescue work?

301
00:17:31,359 --> 00:17:32,440
Yes.

302
00:17:36,039 --> 00:17:38,319
His mom's death was actually quite a big blow to him.

303
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:40,279
He said...

304
00:17:41,039 --> 00:17:42,240
when he was five,

305
00:17:42,559 --> 00:17:44,000
he has already died with his mom.

306
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:46,759
He is living a second life.

307
00:17:47,039 --> 00:17:48,200
So in every rescue,

308
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:51,480
he does it as if he doesn't care about his life.

309
00:17:53,279 --> 00:17:54,480
That's the kind of person he is.

310
00:17:55,559 --> 00:17:57,170
How could he not be pitied?

311
00:18:02,559 --> 00:18:05,559
That's why you became attached to him.

312
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:08,720
I'm not dating him.

313
00:18:10,119 --> 00:18:11,599
I didn't say yes either to his confession.

314
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,759
It has just been so long.

315
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:18,480
I'm used to seeing him every day.

316
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:22,200
I'm used to watching him behave willfully,

317
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,650
make mistakes,

318
00:18:24,319 --> 00:18:25,440
and throw a fit.

319
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:30,119
I witness him calm down bit by bit from instability...

320
00:18:31,170 --> 00:18:32,319
and become mature.

321
00:18:34,079 --> 00:18:35,759
I get confused at times.

322
00:18:37,319 --> 00:18:38,410
I think...

323
00:18:39,599 --> 00:18:41,079
it would be good...

324
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:43,119
to go on like this.

325
00:18:51,559 --> 00:18:52,720
You know what?

326
00:18:53,410 --> 00:18:56,000
When I worked with Hou Jue,

327
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,720
I was quite moved.

328
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:59,170
Under Chen Chen's pressure,

329
00:18:59,170 --> 00:19:00,480
he chose to come back to you.

330
00:19:02,410 --> 00:19:03,759
I thought that...

331
00:19:03,890 --> 00:19:05,440
this lad is really something.

332
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:06,480
It's not just all talk.

333
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:07,890
He really loves you.

334
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,200
At the present,

335
00:19:11,759 --> 00:19:13,890
between you and Chen Chen,

336
00:19:14,279 --> 00:19:15,279
he chose you.

337
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:17,839
But between you and the future,

338
00:19:18,119 --> 00:19:19,410
he gave you up.

339
00:19:24,359 --> 00:19:25,680
It's good that he gave up.

340
00:19:27,519 --> 00:19:28,680
Why should he choose me?

341
00:19:29,079 --> 00:19:31,039
What's in it for him?

342
00:19:31,359 --> 00:19:33,759
Except for safety.

343
00:19:36,279 --> 00:19:37,759
He's on the rise.

344
00:19:38,839 --> 00:19:40,170
Chen Chen is important to him.

345
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:43,359
I think so.

346
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:45,079
It's good that you two are apart now.

347
00:19:45,279 --> 00:19:46,519
He's young.

348
00:19:46,799 --> 00:19:48,759
He's still immature and unstable.

349
00:19:48,759 --> 00:19:50,759
You never know if he would change...

350
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,200
when he has succeeded in the future.

351
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:53,480
At the time,

352
00:19:53,599 --> 00:19:54,759
you would have become attached to him.

353
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:56,039
If he runs away by then,

354
00:19:56,039 --> 00:19:57,170
you will get into trouble.

355
00:20:03,890 --> 00:20:05,079
I know that.

356
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:07,720
Don't worry.

357
00:20:10,839 --> 00:20:12,759
Do you know what I'm thinking right now?

358
00:20:12,759 --> 00:20:13,759
What?

359
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:16,119
You're too small for this place.

360
00:20:16,599 --> 00:20:18,839
Your world is out there.

361
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:22,200
Come on.

362
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:23,759
Let's go and see the outside world.

363
00:20:25,039 --> 00:20:26,079
Give it to me.

364
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:27,799
Give me that.

365
00:20:28,119 --> 00:20:29,119
Put it down.

366
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:31,519
Come on.

367
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,960
(Menu)

368
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:15,279
Ying Nan.

369
00:22:16,079 --> 00:22:17,240
I want to thank Lan Qi.

370
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:19,400
I wanted to treat him to a meal.

371
00:22:19,599 --> 00:22:20,759
Shi Yi is coming too.

372
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:23,440
Shi Yi loves your salad.

373
00:22:24,799 --> 00:22:26,279
But I don't know how to make it.

374
00:22:26,759 --> 00:22:27,880
Teach me.

375
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:35,000
You may use any vegetable...

376
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,160
and any sauce.

377
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:37,839
Just mix it.

378
00:22:41,519 --> 00:22:42,799
Why is it so complicated?

379
00:22:43,759 --> 00:22:44,880
I'm afraid I can't do it.

380
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:47,640
Or I can pick it up when you're done.

381
00:22:48,839 --> 00:22:51,359
Salad tastes better when it's fresh.

382
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:55,119
Why don't you come over and make it for us?

383
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,200
All right then.

384
00:23:01,559 --> 00:23:03,200
I'll leave after I'm done. I'm not joining for dinner.

385
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:04,920
I'll save my money then.

386
00:23:05,599 --> 00:23:06,680
No problem.

387
00:23:16,759 --> 00:23:17,799
Shi Yi.

388
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:20,119
Is there a problem with starting work the day after tomorrow?

389
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:22,279
No problem.

390
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:26,079
You have four people with you.

391
00:23:26,559 --> 00:23:28,559
Teach and guide them well.

392
00:23:28,559 --> 00:23:29,559
Got it.

393
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:33,960
It has been too hard on you for three months.

394
00:23:35,039 --> 00:23:37,799
It so happens that the hotel has nice scenery.

395
00:23:38,119 --> 00:23:40,720
You can relax while you work.

396
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:43,680
All right, enough talking. You may go for lunch now.

397
00:23:45,079 --> 00:23:46,160
Yes.

398
00:23:48,680 --> 00:23:50,200
I miss the food here.

399
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,920
Of course. Get going.

400
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,400
Shi Yi.

401
00:24:05,599 --> 00:24:06,680
Hello.

402
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,240
I'm here.

403
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:30,279
Has the end become the beginning?

404
00:24:30,759 --> 00:24:31,759
What?

405
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,319
I'm talking about Lan Qi.

406
00:24:34,519 --> 00:24:36,839
You two are still in touch.

407
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:38,240
I hope...

408
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:40,000
you can rekindle that old spark.

409
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:43,000
An old spark can't be rekindled.

410
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,359
It would have already rekindled if it is meant to.

411
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:47,000
He's too perfect.

412
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,400
He wants everything to be perfect.

413
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:49,880
That's why it didn't work.

414
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:51,039
It's good to stay friends.

415
00:24:51,359 --> 00:24:53,440
You don't know how lucky you are.

416
00:24:54,079 --> 00:24:55,079
Really?

417
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,440
What a strange place.

418
00:25:10,839 --> 00:25:11,839
Sir.

419
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:14,400
May I ask where Wu Tian Yi lives?

420
00:25:14,559 --> 00:25:16,880
Wu Tian Yi's house is in the last alley.

421
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,880
- Thank you. - Don't mention it.

422
00:25:34,519 --> 00:25:36,319
What a dump.

423
00:25:59,519 --> 00:26:00,519
Hold on.

424
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:04,960
Ying Nan.

425
00:26:05,519 --> 00:26:06,880
How was it? Was it easy to find?

426
00:26:07,519 --> 00:26:09,079
This is such a shabby place.

427
00:26:11,240 --> 00:26:12,599
Shi Yi rented this place.

428
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:14,359
She was going to rent a better place,

429
00:26:14,799 --> 00:26:16,400
but I told her it's okay.

430
00:26:17,039 --> 00:26:18,319
It's well-lit too.

431
00:26:18,319 --> 00:26:19,759
There's a balcony on the second floor.

432
00:26:20,319 --> 00:26:21,319
It's amazing.

433
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:23,599
The point is, it's cheap.

434
00:26:23,839 --> 00:26:26,119
You can only get half the size somewhere else at this price.

435
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:29,319
It's well-organized.

436
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,279
What would you like to drink?

437
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,480
Just plain water.

438
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,599
You've started buying flowers.

439
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:42,839
No. Today...

440
00:26:43,799 --> 00:26:44,839
Yes.

441
00:26:45,160 --> 00:26:46,279
I've started buying flowers.

442
00:26:47,519 --> 00:26:48,559
Have some water.

443
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:50,759
Don't bother.

444
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:52,359
It's getting late. Let's cook.

445
00:26:53,319 --> 00:26:54,319
Take a look.

446
00:27:03,039 --> 00:27:05,039
Are you ready? What do you want me to do?

447
00:27:05,279 --> 00:27:06,480
Just make a salad.

448
00:27:06,759 --> 00:27:08,119
I'll do everything else.

449
00:27:10,279 --> 00:27:11,720
Then I'll just be prepared to eat.

450
00:27:53,759 --> 00:27:54,839
Thank you.

451
00:27:55,039 --> 00:27:56,039
I'm leaving.

452
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:57,960
Mom.

453
00:27:58,400 --> 00:27:59,400
Shi Yi.

454
00:27:59,519 --> 00:28:00,680
Why are you here?

455
00:28:01,759 --> 00:28:02,839
Well...

456
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:04,359
Your dad asked me to cook.

457
00:28:04,359 --> 00:28:05,359
I...

458
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:07,680
I was borrowing some green onions. Let's go.

459
00:28:08,839 --> 00:28:09,920
What's going on?

460
00:28:10,279 --> 00:28:12,200
Nothing. Let's eat.

461
00:28:12,839 --> 00:28:13,960
These are all your favorites.

462
00:28:14,079 --> 00:28:15,279
Dad, are you cooking?

463
00:28:15,440 --> 00:28:17,240
I made your favorite coconut chicken.

464
00:28:17,559 --> 00:28:18,640
It's my mom's favorite, right?

465
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,559
Mr. Wu, the table is done.

466
00:28:21,599 --> 00:28:22,599
Lan Qi.

467
00:28:22,759 --> 00:28:24,599
- You're back. - Lan Qi, why are you here?

468
00:28:25,279 --> 00:28:27,000
I'm learning how to cook from Mr. Wu.

469
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:30,400
The table is set. You may go first.

470
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:31,400
We'll handle the rest.

471
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:32,480
- All right. - Go up.

472
00:28:32,480 --> 00:28:33,519
Thank you for your hard work.

473
00:28:33,519 --> 00:28:35,079
The two of us will just wait for the food.

474
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:36,319
Come on.

475
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:37,880
- Lan Qi, come on. - Mom.

476
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:39,200
- What's next? - Why is Lan Qi here?

477
00:28:39,200 --> 00:28:41,359
- Take this chicken to the table. - All right, let me do it.

478
00:28:41,359 --> 00:28:42,920
Your dad is treating Lan Qi to a meal.

479
00:28:43,359 --> 00:28:44,720
Let's go.

480
00:28:47,599 --> 00:28:48,680
There's a lot.

481
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:50,759
Drink that.

482
00:28:50,759 --> 00:28:52,160
I don't drink wine. I'll just drink this.

483
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:56,720
Come, let's eat.

484
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:02,720
Here, Lan Qi, have a drink.

485
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:03,720
Thank you, Ms. Zhang.

486
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:06,160
Go on, try it.

487
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:08,160
That's enough.

488
00:29:08,559 --> 00:29:09,599
It's okay to drink more.

489
00:29:09,599 --> 00:29:10,599
All right.

490
00:29:10,799 --> 00:29:11,880
Here.

491
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:18,079
Not bad. You have mastered his skills.

492
00:29:18,599 --> 00:29:19,720
I think they forgot to add salt.

493
00:29:21,599 --> 00:29:22,599
No, I did.

494
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,680
We did. You liar.

495
00:29:25,039 --> 00:29:26,119
I'm kidding.

496
00:29:26,119 --> 00:29:27,519
It's good. Better than me anyway.

497
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:28,720
Look at her.

498
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:31,400
I only pass down my cooking skill to men.

499
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:33,920
Come on.

500
00:29:35,759 --> 00:29:37,759
You talk as if you are a master chef.

501
00:29:39,279 --> 00:29:40,440
The boasting one.

502
